<body>

    <h2>TÜV SÜD GRC Connect Knowledge Base - Dashboards</h2>

    <div id="content" class="setPrimary">
        <div id="contentInner">

            <div id="introduction" class="content">
                <h2>Introduction</h2>
                <p class="contentP">
                   Organizations require sufficient risk management measures to minimize their exposures and potential for losses. With increasing regulatory and insurance requirements, 
                    it is more important than ever to have proper controls and measures in place. To do this, the proper identification, evaluation and development of mitigation options is a must for 
                    companies looking to minimize their risk. We support you with high quality risk analysis and in-depth risk management programs to help you to reduce your property loss history and expectancy, 
                    and ensure safety and reliability for the future.
                    <br /><br />
                    The TÜV SÜD GRC Connect Dashboards provide clients with the business intelligence necessary to help meet these goals.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div id="dashboardRecs" class="content">
                <h2>Dashboards</h2>
                <p class="contentP">
                    Click a dashboard to see more details about the selected dashboard.<br />
                </p>
                <p>
                    <a href="BuildYourOwn.aspx">Build Your Own<br /><img src="images/BuildYourOwnDashboard.jpg" style="border:1px solid #CFD8DC; width:360px;height:217px" /></a><br /><br />
                    <a href="Infrared.aspx">Infrared<br /><img src="images/IR.jpg" style="border:1px solid #CFD8DC; width:360px;height:217px" /></a><br /><br />
                    <a href="Inspections.aspx">Inspections<br /><img src="images/Insp.jpg" style="border:1px solid #CFD8DC; width:360px;height:217px" /></a><br /><br />
                    <a href="Ratings.aspx">Ratings<br /><img src="images/RatingsDashboard.jpg" style="border:1px solid #CFD8DC; width:360px;height:217px" /></a><br /><br />
                    <a href="Recommendations.aspx">Recommendations<br /><img src="images/RecsDashboard.jpg" style="border:1px solid #CFD8DC; width:360px;height:217px" /></a>
                </p>
            </div>

            <div id="dashboardControls" class="content">
                <h2>Dashboard Controls</h2>
                <p class="contentP">
                    There are a variety of controls in the dashboards to help you to get the information you need.
                </p>
                    <img src="images/Controls.jpg"  style="width:50%;float:left;border:1px solid #CFD8DC" />
                    <ul style="float:left;width:40%;">
                    <li>
                        Select a different dashboard using the Report Category and Report dropdowns.  Click Show Report when done with the selection.  The Full Screen button will show the dashboard in full screen mode.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        The Information icon displays this help document.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Opening the filter panel will allow you to filter the data on a wide number of fields depending upon the dashboard being viewed.  Close the filter panel when done making your selections.  
                        To select more than one item in the dropdowns, hold down the "Ctrl" key while clicking items.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Some dashboards will have multiple pages.  The paging control enables you to move between the pages.
                    </li>
                    </ul>
            </div>

            <div id="controls1" class="content">
                <h3>Filter Panel</h3>
                <p class="contentP">
                    The Filter Panel allows the user to apply filters to the charts and data on the current dashboard tab.
                </p>
                    <img src="images/ControlsFilter.jpg" style="float:left;border:1px solid #CFD8DC" />
                    <ul style="float:left;width:40%;">
                    <li>
                        Each dashboard tab could have different fields that are available for filtering.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Filters will consist of dropdown selections and text boxes.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                       To choose multiple items in a dropdown, hold the Ctrl key down while selecting items.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                       When done, close the Filter Panel by clicking the gray filter panel bar.
                    </li>
                    </ul>
            </div>

            <div id="controls2" class="content">
                <h3>Slicers</h3>
                <p class="contentP">
                    A Slicer is another control that allows the user to apply filters to the charts and data on the current dashboard tab.
                </p>
                    <img src="images/ControlsSlicers.jpg" style="float:left;border:1px solid #CFD8DC" />
                    <ul style="float:left;width:40%;">
                    <li>
                        A dashboard tab might have Slicers available for additional filtering (left).  
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Opening a slicer will allow the user to choose one or more filter values (right).  
                        To choose multiple items in a dropdown, hold the Ctrl key down while selecting items.
                    </li>
                    </ul>
            </div>

            <div id="controls3" class="content">
                <h3>Chart Controls</h3>
                <p class="contentP">
                    Moving the mouse over any individual chart (shown below in the Recommendation Risk Improvement chart) will cause the chart controls (outlined in red) to appear.
                </p>
                    <img src="images/ControlsChart.jpg" style="float:left;border:1px solid #CFD8DC" />
                    <ul style="float:left;width:40%;">
                    <li>
                        Move the mouse over the Filter icon to display the current filter that is applied to the data in the chart.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Click the Focus Mode icon to expand the view of the current chart.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                       Click the elipses (...) to display other options that are appropriate for the selected chart.  This may allow the user to export the data, show the data as a table, 
                        sort the data, or make use of other functionality. 
                    </li>
                    </ul>
            </div>

            <div id="controls4" class="content">
                <h3>More Options</h3>
                <p class="contentP">
                    The "More Options" sub-menu item provides more functionality.
                </p>
                    <img src="images/ControlsMoreOptions.jpg" style="float:left;border:1px solid #CFD8DC" />
                    <ul style="float:left;width:40%;">
                    <li>
                        When viewing a grid of data, an Export Data menu item may be available for exporting the data.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Use one of the sorting options to change the order in which the data is presented.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                       Spotlighting on the control will maximize the control for improved viewing.
                    </li>
                    </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

</body>
</html>
